  "optimization_notes": "Root cause: most hot time comes from touching wide num columns and initializing anti-join resources before establishing whether the 2023 ddate window yields any rows; this is a Category C work-elimination fix with plan restructuring. The plan now makes ddate the first-stage scan key, materializes candidate rowids, applies uom/value only on candidates, and defers loading/using pre anti-join structures and join key columns unless survivors exist, eliminating unnecessary random lookups and reducing loaded bytes on likely-empty windows.",
